m discipline.  If more people send their kids to public school, will parents suddenly stop denying their child is bullying other kids or punish them for disrepecting their teachers?  I doubt it!  If I have a child with a strong aptitude in science, and I have the option (and money) to choose between a public school or a private science academy, I'm going to make the best choice for my kid.  That doesn't make me a bad person! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="736" language="en" documentId="2985" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Meli Ann" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:55PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="7" thumbsDown="0" origId="2985" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="736"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>